The paper deals with the problem of multi-robot target assignment, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of multiple sub-fields in computer science. The use of the term "robotic networks" in the title suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) sub-category, which deals with the coordination and interaction of multiple agents or robots. The paper also discusses the use of communication and sensing ranges, which are common concepts in the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The use of optimization techniques and approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also deals with the concept of hierarchical communication, which is a topic that falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the use of strategies and formulas for computing the number of robots needed suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
